    "description": "BSE Global Group is actively seeking a talented and motivated Senior Financial Analyst to join our dynamic team in Howrah. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout BSE Global Group:\nBSE Global Group is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Manage accounts payable and accounts receivable functions\n• Prepare annual reports and investor presentations\n• Monitor financial performance against targets and provide variance analysis\n• Maintain general ledger and ensure accurate bookkeeping\n• Process payroll and manage employee reimbursements\n• Prepare MIS reports for senior management review\n• Manage credit risk assessment and loan appraisal processes\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• MBA from a recognized university\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Due Diligence\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n• Proficiency in Tally\n• Proficiency in QuickBooks\n• Proficiency in Income Tax\n• Proficiency in Ind AS\n• Proficiency in Budgeting\n• Proficiency in Risk Management\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Howrah, West Bengal, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with BSE Global Group!",
